TY  - JOUR
TI  - Recursively Decentralized Decision Making
AU  - Blackorby, Charles
AU  - Nissen, David
AU  - Primont, Daniel
AU  - Russell, R. Robert
AB  - [Decentralized decision making is consistent if it is executed without cost (i.e., without a loss of output or utility). Consistency requires that the objective function be appropriately structured. In this paper, a hierarchical decision making structure is rationalized by an objective function which combines some of the properties of homothetic separability and asymmetric separability.]
